de.rincewind.api.gui.elements

Interface ElementSwitcher<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - specifying the object-type
    All Superinterfaces:
    Element, ElementButton, ElementDisplayable, ElementSizeable, EventBased, java.lang.Iterable<ElementSwitcher.SwitchItem<T>>, Sizeable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CraftElementSwitcher, Elements.ElementSwitcherExtendable

    public interface ElementSwitcher<T>
extends ElementButton, java.lang.Iterable<ElementSwitcher.SwitchItem<T>>
    This element allows the suer to switch through items, added to this element. Its an infinite loop by clicking on the 'switcher'. With right-click you can switch forward and with left-click you can switch backward. By shift-click you can skip one entry and jump 2 items forward or backward. For a better handling with this element, you can 'save' an object from an specified type in each switch-entry. This element implements Iterable to iterate throw all added entries.
    Since:
    2.3.3
    Author:
    Rincewind34
    See Also:
    Elements.ElementSwitcherExtendable
